yaccviso is an excellent tool for generating graphs of the parser bnf:
http://lo-res.org/~aaron/yaccviso/

atul's mini c compiler in python provided some interesting hints:
http://people.cs.uchicago.edu/~varmaa/mini_c/

Tom Niemann's "A compact guide to Lex and Yacc" is indispensible 

